  { id: "crm", label: "CRM & Communication" },
  { id: "integrations", label: "Integrations" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Verdict" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQ" }
];
const faqItems = [
  { q: "Which is cheaper, Housecall Pro or Jobber?", a: "For solo operators, Jobber is cheaper ($39/month vs $59/month). For teams of 5, pricing is nearly identical ($149-$169/month). For teams of 10+, Housecall Pro's MAX plan can be cheaper than Jobber's per-user model depending on your quote." },
  { q: "Which has a better mobile app?", a: "Both have strong mobile apps. Jobber's iOS app is rated 4.8/5 and is consistently praised for speed and reliability. Housecall Pro's app is rated 4.7/5 with stronger customer communication features. Both work offline for basic functions." },
  { q: "Can I switch from Housecall Pro to Jobber (or vice versa)?", a: "Yes. Both platforms support CSV data export. The typical migration takes 1-2 weeks. Both offer free trials so you can test the new platform before canceling the old one." },
  { q: "Which integrates better with QuickBooks?", a: "Neither platform includes QuickBooks on their entry-level plans. Jobber requires Connect ($119/month) and Housecall Pro requires Essentials ($149/month). Users report Jobber's QuickBooks sync is slightly more reliable, while Housecall Pro's integration occasionally creates duplicates that need manual cleanup." },
  { q: "Which is better for HVAC specifically?", a: "Both serve HVAC well. Jobber has stronger route optimization (reducing drive time between jobs) and job costing (tracking profitability per job). Housecall Pro has better customer-facing tools (online booking, automated reviews, text notifications). Pick based on which gap matters more in your operation." }
];
