<ArticleLayout
  title="Housecall Pro vs Jobber for HVAC Companies (2026): Pricing, Features, and Verdict — HVAC Software Hub"
  description="Detailed comparison of Housecall Pro and Jobber for HVAC companies. Side-by-side pricing, features, mobile apps, and which platform fits your team size."
  canonicalPath="/hvac/crm/housecall-pro-vs-jobber"
  category="Comparisons"
  publishDate="2026-04-06"
  readTime="13 min read"
  intent="BOFU"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
<div class="container py-8">
  <div class="flex gap-12">
    <article class="flex-1 min-w-0 max-w-3xl">

      <div class="prose mt-8">
        <p>Housecall Pro and Jobber are the two most popular field service platforms for small HVAC companies. They are priced similarly, offer overlapping features, and both have free trials. This makes the choice difficult unless you know exactly where they differ.</p>
        <p>We evaluated both platforms across six categories that matter most to HVAC operations. Here is where each one wins and loses.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose" id="pricing">
        <h2>Pricing Comparison</h2>
      </div>
      <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin: 16px 0; font-size: 14px;">
